# Cursor Rules — Salary Sister AI

## Project Overview

Salary Sister AI — a Spanish-language financial empowerment platform helping women analyze salary gaps and negotiate better compensation. Hackathon project ("She Ships").

All UI text must be in Spanish (`lang="es"`).

## Commands

- Dev server: `pnpm dev` (localhost:3000)
- Build: `pnpm build`
- Lint: `pnpm lint` (ESLint 9)
- Package manager: pnpm

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16, App Router, React 19
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4 (`@tailwindcss/postcss`)
- Geist font via `next/font/google`
- Supabase via `@supabase/supabase-js`

## Architecture

- App Router in `src/app/` — React Server Components by default
- Path alias: `@/*` → `./src/*`
- Routes: landing (`/`), `/salary-input`, `/reality-check`

### Key files

- `src/app/salary-input/actions.ts` — Server actions (Supabase inserts)
- `src/components/Header.tsx`, `Footer.tsx` — Shared layout components
- `src/lib/supabase.ts` — Supabase server-side client (NEVER import in client components)
- `src/types/database.ts` — TypeScript interfaces matching Supabase tables
- `src/app/globals.css` — Design tokens (@theme inline)

### Supabase

- Table: `salary_submissions` (22 columns — see `FIELD_MAPPING.md`)
- Types: `SalarySubmission` / `SalarySubmissionInsert`
- Client is server-side only — uses `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY`
- Env vars in `.env.local` (template: `.env.example`)

### Server Actions Pattern

```typescript
"use server";
import { supabase } from "@/lib/supabase";
// Return { success: boolean; error?: string }
// Use FormData, nullable fields with || null
// Booleans from checkboxes: === "on"
```

## Design Tokens (Tailwind v4)

USE THESE — not generic Tailwind colors:

Text: `text-ink`, `text-ink-secondary`, `text-ink-muted`, `text-ink-faint`
Surfaces: `bg-parchment`, `bg-surface`, `bg-surface-elevated`
Brand: `bg-plum`, `bg-plum-deep`, `bg-plum-light`
Accent: `bg-valor`, `bg-valor-light`, `bg-valor-subtle`
Semantic: `text-warmth`, `text-growth`, `text-gap`
Borders: `border-border`, `border-border-strong`

## Coding Conventions

- Tailwind utility classes with project design tokens only
- Icons: `lucide-react`
- `"use client"` only when state or browser APIs needed
- Server logic stays in `actions.ts`, never in client components
- Forms use consistent input/select/textarea styling (see `/salary-input/page.tsx`)
- No generic Tailwind colors — always use the custom tokens
